commitResults.messageTitle: Unable to keep track of commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Keep track of commands so users can see past inputs

Added array in Command class to keep track of past input and list when called

list and bye command are not added in tracking of past commands

majority of commands is a form of task and they have similar behavior(e.g. isDone and have a description)

To allow for future polymorphisms where there are different types of tasks that is being tracked

commitResults.messageBody: commands can be directly processed by Duke class
commands are now processed by Duke class

commitResults.messageTitle: Added text to match expected output when calling list. Changed to print "added input" where input is the whole input and not only the first word. Simplified some logic in the program

commitResults.messageBody:
To allow future classes to inherit from

added way to identify type of task and indicate whether is completed

to allow printing of output just by calling identity method

Deadline inherits from Task. Deadline is a task with extra fields(e.g. the due date of said task)

Overrided identify so as differentiate deadline from tasks

ToDo is a form of task. Similar fields and behavior

Overrided identify so as to  differentiate ToDo from Task

Event class is a Task thus it inherits from Task
Override identify class to differentiate Task from Events.
Extra field of deadline to indicate the due date of event

commitResults.messageTitle: Added extensions to commands so as to accomodate new classes(i.e. Task, ToDo, Event and Deadline)
commitResults.messageBody:
processedCommand is further processed to obtain deadline and description which are used to create Event and/or Deadline instances
Logic of printing whether task is marked or unmarked is now handle by the individual classes(Event,Deadline,ToDo,Task)
